# .graphifyignore — same syntax as .gitignore (with ! negation).
# Tells graphify what NOT to index when building the engine knowledge
# graph at ./graphify-out/. See ADR-016-EngineGraph.md and AGENTS.md
# § "Engine Graph (graphify)".
#
# Fallback behaviour (per graphify docs):
# - .gitignore is respected automatically.
# - If no .graphifyignore is present, graphify falls back to the
#   nearest .gitignore.
# - If both exist in a directory, .graphifyignore takes priority.
# - Subdirectory scoping works the same way as git.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Legacy Laravel codebase (frozen; schoolify graph covers it separately)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
schoolify/
schoolify/**

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Engine authoring guidelines (the docs we used to write the current docs)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
docs_guidlines/
docs_guidlines/**

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build outputs
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
target/
**/target/

# Cargo lock + build artefacts that are not source
Cargo.lock

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Git internals
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.git/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Graph artefacts (the engine graph is the output, not input)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
graphify-out/cache/
graphify-out/cost.json
graphify-out/.graphify_*
# Note: graphify-out/graph.html, graph.json, manifest.json,
# GRAPH_REPORT.md ARE indexed / committed (per graphify convention).
# The .gitignore at the repo root excludes graphify-out/cost.json
# (the only local-only artefact).
